point because it points towards an eye-related condition.","dimension":11,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.060956,0.078415,0.088297,0.09746,0.095661,0.094252,0.095936,0.088305,0.083154,0.083831,0.072541,0.061193],"unified_progress":[0.049249,0.07285,0.086324,0.09708,0.098401,0.096152,0.097891,0.093921,0.089387,0.086763,0.073428,0.058553]},{"section":11,"text":"The visual field test showed a significant field defect.","dimension":1,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035704,0.068945,0.091449,0.11614,0.1124,0.1127,0.10993,0.098174,0.081454,0.067286,0.057795,0.048023],"unified_progress":[0.038495,0.075201,0.093878,0.10885,0.10885,0.1035,0.099136,0.091928,0.090932,0.073948,0.062109,0.053169]},{"section":12,"text":"Visual field defects can be caused by various issues like glaucoma, optic neuritis, or brain lesions affecting the visual pathways.","dimension":3,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031105,0.059961,0.08241,0.10062,0.10587,0.10741,0.11245,0.10298,0.092954,0.085886,0.065808,0.052547],"unified_progress":[0.032659,0.067109,0.088702,0.10256,0.10471,0.11169,0.10717,0.099086,0.092154,0.083061,0.064961,0.046132]},{"section":13,"text":"Since he's a child, it's more likely something that affects the optic nerve or the visual pathways in the brain.","dimension":3,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.042296,0.061565,0.077962,0.089476,0.094429,0.097729,0.10243,0.09949,0.095405,0.094842,0.079101,0.065272],"unified_progress":[0.044103,0.06938,0.083108,0.092748,0.097021,0.098913,0.099717,0.098702,0.093701,0.089581,0.075038,0.057988]},{"section":14,"text":"The CT scan of the head showed a suprasellar mass with calcification.","dimension":1,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.024302,0.060196,0.089334,0.11294,0.1193,0.12174,0.12025,0.10612,0.084249,0.065788,0.054016,0.041772],"unified_progress":[0.031979,0.074271,0.096524,0.10961,0.11457,0.10742,0.10193,0.09332,0.09549,0.071144,0.057515,0.046223]},{"section":15,"text":"The supraseller area is just above the sella turcica, which is the area where the pituitary gland is located.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03225,0.057491,0.077987,0.09215,0.10588,0.1124,0.11343,0.10966,0.099162,0.082287,0.064899,0.052413],"unified_progress":[0.03604,0.065968,0.08516,0.099169,0.10304,0.12335,0.10577,0.097635,0.09132,0.080554,0.063303,0.048692]},{"section":16,"text":"Calcification in this area could indicate a tumor, maybe a craniopharyngeal ganglioma, which is a type of brain tumor that affects children.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028073,0.04924,0.070469,0.08542,0.099858,0.10746,0.11205,0.1126,0.10606,0.093683,0.073708,0.061381],"unified_progress":[0.031894,0.061026,0.08343,0.097652,0.10241,0.11366,0.10825,0.10228,0.095201,0.086181,0.06772,0.050299]},{"section":17,"text":"These tumors can cause pressure on nearby structures, including the optic chiasm, which is responsible for the visual field.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028575,0.046237,0.065134,0.079558,0.097531,0.10786,0.11289,0.11671,0.11192,0.094702,0.076107,0.062772],"unified_progress":[0.031978,0.058249,0.080843,0.095975,0.10244,0.11228,0.10949,0.10449,0.097614,0.08834,0.06827,0.050034]},{"section":18,"text":"Putting this together: a suprasellar mass with calcification in a young child, along with visual field defects and diminished acuity, points towards a craniopharyngeal ganglioma.","dimension":4,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.023827,0.038197,0.049488,0.058534,0.064682,0.071323,0.077593,0.086657,0.094613,0.10864,0.13408,0.19237],"unified_progress":[0.02413,0.040819,0.051491,0.062424,0.067805,0.080365,0.080456,0.091347,0.097208,0.10034,0.13356,0.17006]},{"section":19,"text":"This tumor can press on the optic chiasm, causing vision problems.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.027282,0.039347,0.0533,0.06464,0.078144,0.088447,0.09697,0.10552,0.11077,0.10825,0.10614,0.12119],"unified_progress":[0.02783,0.045882,0.062571,0.074424,0.083149,0.09567,0.096886,0.10232,0.10386,0.10323,0.10144,0.10274]},{"section":20,"text":"The fact that his cognitive functions are normal and his grades are good might mean the tumor isn't causing significant brain damage or affecting other cognitive functions, but it's still a concerning finding.","dimension":5,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034924,0.048388,0.063168,0.070959,0.077561,0.085478,0.092646,0.1004,0.10607,0.11061,0.11048,0.099316],"unified_progress":[0.039137,0.055722,0.0646,0.071699,0.081278,0.087448,0.091856,0.10105,0.10362,0.11247,0.10221,0.08891]},{"section":21,"text":"I don't think it's something like optic neuritis because that usually comes with other symptoms like eye pain or redness, which aren't mentioned here.","dimension":5,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.018163,0.04284,0.063987,0.073818,0.080551,0.090003,0.097454,0.10986,0.11654,0.12129,0.11494,0.070552],"unified_progress":[0.022646,0.0475,0.063303,0.073362,0.087507,0.092583,0.10143,0.11165,0.11423,0.12566,0.10145,0.058691]},{"section":22,"text":"Glaucoma in a child is rare and usually associated with other symptoms too.","dimension":5,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.021651,0.041983,0.062071,0.073468,0.081917,0.09256,0.098764,0.11177,0.11752,0.11876,0.10987,0.069671],"unified_progress":[0.025642,0.049473,0.065974,0.07662,0.088769,0.096432,0.10267,0.11214,0.11258,0.11948,0.095274,0.054939]},{"section":23,"text":"So, the most likely diagnosis is a craniopharyngeal ganglioma.","dimension":4,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.019522,0.035077,0.048058,0.057572,0.064072,0.071412,0.078803,0.089501,0.09948,0.11371,0.13699,0.18581],"unified_progress":[0.020505,0.03874,0.050097,0.060773,0.066733,0.076945,0.081242,0.091252,0.097446,0.10512,0.13416,0.17698]}],"deepseek-r1-distill-qwen-14b":[{"section":